Keep safe, and remember that if we're asking you to do something it's because we have to. Staff want this to be over and to be safe too.
At both of these places, please don't mix with other groups. It's unsafe and also means you'll be standing in the way of customers and staff moving around the building.
You also need to keep your mask on in a theatre even if there's no one within 2 metres of you, for instance if you have box seats. I disagree with this but hey, that's the rules.

We ask that one person from each group goes to the bar. If you're exempt, again, make it clear, both for us and the audience around you.

When you're drinking take your mask down to drink, then put it back up. Please don't take your mask off just because you're holding a drink.

We don't serve food in theatres yet, but we do serve drinks. Often theatres have a bar on each level, so there's no need to keep moving around the building. Again, they may also have an ordering app, which lets you collect your drink directly rather than joining the queue.

At a theatre, the seats are 1 metre apart. Rows have been removed and seats blocked out on both sides of each booking. This is allowed with "robust mitigations" - ie, you keep your mask on in your seat. Though after a year of trying to stay 2m+ away, it may feel very close.

Everywhere does table service, and many have apps too. Smaller places will likely get you to pay for each order rather than setting up a tab. Feel free to ask your server questions, it's what we do all day. Just understand we are not the ones putting these rules in place.

At a dining establishment where the seats are 2m+ apart, you can have your mask off when seated. Please put it back on as soon as you're not seated. If you're exempt, please wear something that makes this clear, and we will try to seat you by the door for your health and others'.

If you go to any venue please either have the NHS app on your phone, or understand that we're going to need you to give your name and contact info some other way. The other ways may be writing them down, or texting a number, or going to a website. We have to ask every individual.
